This is primarily an SPI to allow Spring Security to align its pattern matching with the same pattern matching that would be used in Spring MVC for a given request, in order to avoid security issues. Use of this introspector should be avoided for other purposes because it incurs the overhead of resolving the handler for a request.

This interface is used to allow the {@link DispatcherServlet} to be indefinitely extensible. The {@code DispatcherServlet} accesses all installed handlers through this interface, meaning that it does not contain code specific to any handler type.
